    "content": "# Flask Microservices\n\n    ## What it is\n    Flask Microservices covers Flask backend development: flask microservices, request lifecycle, APIs, middleware, auth, database, frontend integration, and deployment. The goal is to understand the concept well enough to implement it, debug it, and explain it in an interview.\n\n    ## Why it exists\n    It exists because real applications need predictable structure, maintainable code, clear boundaries, error handling, and production behavior rather than only happy-path snippets.\n\n    ## Mental model\n    ```mermaid\n    flowchart TD\n A[Client] --> B[WSGI server]\n B --> C[Flask app]\n C --> D[before_request/decorator]\n D --> E[Route]\n E --> F[Service/DB]\n F --> G[Response]\n    ```\n\n    ## Core concepts\n    - Definition and role in the stack.\n    - Input/output boundary.\n    - Runtime behavior.\n    - Failure behavior.\n    - Common abstractions.\n    - Production trade-offs.\n\n    ## Practical example\n    ```python\n    from flask import Flask, request, jsonify\nfrom functools import wraps\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\ndef login_required(fn):\n    @wraps(fn)\n    def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):\n        if not request.headers.get(\"Authorization\"):\n            return jsonify({\"error\":\"missing token\"}), 401\n        return fn(*args, **kwargs)\n    return wrapper\n\n@app.post(\"/items\")\n@login_required\ndef create_item():\n    return jsonify(request.get_json() or {}), 201\n    ```\n\n    ## Common mistakes\n    - Mixing unrelated responsibilities.\n    - Handling only success path.\n    - Ignoring validation, errors, and cleanup.\n    - Not thinking about scale and observability.\n    - Memorizing syntax without mental model.\n\n    ## Production notes\n    Use clear project structure, consistent error shapes, logging, tests, environment config, and separation between transport layer, business logic, and persistence.\n\n    ## Interview explanation\n    Start with what it is, why it exists, how it works internally, then give a practical example and a production caveat.\n\n    ## Flask-specific depth\nCover WSGI lifecycle, app factory, blueprints, request.args/request.get_json/request.form/request.files, decorators, before_request/after_request/teardown_request, SQLAlchemy sessions, CORS, JWT/session auth, Celery/RQ, Gunicorn, Nginx, Docker, ECS deployment, and React/Jinja integration.\n"
